HEADWORD: Aid-de-camp
<hw>Aid"-de-camp`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Aids-de-camp</plw>. <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[F. <ets>aide de
camp</ets> (literally) camp assistant.]</ety> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>An
officer selected by a general to carry orders, also to assist or
represent him in correspondence and in directing movements.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aider</ent>⟦br⟧
